      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Aside from standard interest accrual, look closely at whether you are making any scheduled payments versus extra principal-only payments. Some loan programs, particularly if you are in forbearance or deferment, can accrue interest that gets added to your principal balance, known as capitalization. Another factor is if you are in a repayment plan that emphasizes extended terms rather than aggressive payoff.",
